rdnet und in ihrer Binnenstruktur nach einem einheitlichen Konzept gegliedert. So eignet sich das Handbuch insbesondere auch als Nachschlagewerk.  aThe Council of Europe’s “European Charter for Regional or Minority Languages” is in effect in 25 nations today. This guide systematically describes the status of language policy in these countries, and how the charter is being applied.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLanguage policyzEuropevCongresses. 0aLinguistic minoritiesxLegal status, laws, etczEuropevCongresses. 4aEthnische Minderheit. 4aGesetzgebung. 4aSprachplanung. 4aSprachpolitik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aEthnic Minorities.  aLanguage Planning.  aLanguage Policy.  aLegislation.1 aBarkijević, Ivana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerger, Tilman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCremer, Désirée, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDahmen, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoleschal, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuke, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEickmans, Heinz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFischer, Roswitha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerner, Zsuzsanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLebsanft, Franz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLebsanft, Franz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMüller, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNuolijärvi, Pirkko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 